Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.00,0:00:26.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs100\t(,\fs110)\frz1\fad(3000,500)\fsp0\fscx120\pos(960,800)\b0\shad0\bord0}地          球          脉          动
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.82,0:00:36.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们陆地的边缘都是浅海域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Our planet's continents are fringed by shallow seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.46,0:00:43.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们挨着大陆架 很少地超过200米深\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Rarely more than two hundred meters deep they lie on the continental shelves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.10,0:00:46.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大陆架有时可能延伸达几百英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}which may stretch sometimes for hundreds of miles
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.38,0:00:50.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再往下就是漆黑的深渊\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}before the sea floor drops into deeper darker waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.42,0:01:00.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管浅水域仅仅占据了8%的海洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All together they constitute a mere eight percent of the world's oceans
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.02,0:01:05.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过大多数的海洋生物都生活在这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they contain the vast majority of it's marine life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.75,0:01:13.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs135\fsp6\fad(1000,1000)\pos(963,940)\shad0\bord0}多        样        浅        海
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.00,0:01:20.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs60\fsp5\fad(1000,1000)\pos(960,1080)\bord0\shad3}画 外 音\N{\fs90}大卫 · 爱登堡   爵士
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.78,0:01:43.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一只雄性座头鲸正在用歌声吸引雌鲸来交配\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A male humpback whale sings to attract a mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.82,0:02:10.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,座头鲸刚刚回到它的热带地区的浅海繁殖地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The whales have just returned to their breeding grounds in the shallow seas of the tropics.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.46,0:02:21.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幼鲸才刚刚几周大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The calf is no more than a few weeks old.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.94,0:02:35.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然已经三米长,一吨重 还是比较虚弱,也容易受攻击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Despite being three meters long and weighing nearly a ton, he is nonetheless vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.66,0:02:41.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过幸好有妈妈照料\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but his mother watches over him
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.94,0:02:47.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,疲劳的幼鲸被妈妈托上浮上水面好让它呼吸空气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and, as he begins to tire, she supports him close to the surface so that he can breathe more easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.42,0:03:15.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,赤道附近的浅海是个非常理想的托儿所\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These shallows around the equator are excellent nurseries.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.14,0:03:20.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,温暖,平静,很少有掠食者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're warm, calm, and contain very few predators.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.78,0:03:28.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,顽皮的小座头鲸每天要喝500公升奶\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The playful calf is now drinking five hundred liters of milk a day
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.06,0:03:31.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是它的妈妈却饿的要死\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but his mother must starve.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.70,0:03:34.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里母鲸没有东西可以吃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There is nothing for her to eat here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.10,0:03:43.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和多数热带浅海域一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Like many tropical shallow seas
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.22,0:03:47.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这片明净的水域实际上没有什么生机\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}these crystal clear waters are virtually lifeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.86,0:03:53.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然充满阳光 但是这里主要缺少浮游生物生长所需的养分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They receive year round sunlight but they lack the nutrients essential for the growth of plankton.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.94,0:03:57.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母座头鲸接下来要困在这里大约5个月\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The mother will be trapped here for the next five months
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.82,0:04:03.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,等到小鲸足够强壮了,才开始到极地进食点的旅行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}until her calf is strong enough to make the journey to the feeding grounds, near the poles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.14,0:04:30.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,珊瑚礁是荒凉海洋中的绿洲\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Coral reefs are oases in a watery desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.30,0:04:34.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多数热带浅海比较荒凉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Most tropical shallows are barren
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.22,0:04:40.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过珊瑚礁汇聚着地球上四分之一的海洋生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but these coral havens contain one quarter of all the marine life on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.98,0:05:02.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,珊瑚礁是珊瑚虫的产物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Reefs are the work of polyps
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.58,0:05:05.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一种象小海葵的有机生命群体\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}tiny colonial animals like minute sea anemones
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.46,0:05:11.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可是它们生成的大堡礁甚至可以在月球上看到\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}yet the great barrier reef is so big it can be seen from the Moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.14,0:05:22.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大堡礁由超过2000个独立珊瑚礁组成\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's actually two thousand separate reefs that together
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.00,0:05:30.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,绵延在澳大利亚东北部海岸,长度超过1000公里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}form a barrier stretching for over a thousand miles along Australia's northeastern coast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.02,0:05:34.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不管有多大\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Despite it's vast size
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.30,0:05:39.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里珊瑚礁也不可能容纳全部的海洋生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}this reef does not contain the greatest variety of marine life on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.10,0:05:44.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们去印度尼西亚的北部看看\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}For that one must travel north to Indonesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.58,0:06:19.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,印度尼西亚的这些珊瑚礁 所容纳的各种鱼类几乎跟全加勒比海一样多\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are individual reefs in Indonesia that contain almost as many kinds of fish as live in the whole of the Caribbean.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.78,0:06:26.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且珊瑚物种也要多十倍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There are also ten times the number of coral species.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.54,0:06:36.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,珊瑚在一种微生植物的帮助下生长-海藻 是居住在珊瑚虫里的一种共生藻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Corals thrive in these waters with the help of microscopic plants, algae that grow within the tissues of the polyps
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.10,0:06:47.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,珊瑚虫利用触手抓食经过它身边的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the polyps feed by snaring passing morsels with their tentacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.10,0:07:05.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到了晚上,共生藻停止工作 珊瑚开始释放更多的触手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At night, the algae are inactive but then, the polyps put out even more tentacles
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.22,0:07:09.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样,珊瑚虫可以昼夜不断地有效进食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so coral in effect feeds around the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.22,0:07:29.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种完美平衡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This well balanced alliance brings benefits
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.78,0:07:32.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不仅有益于给珊瑚虫和藻类\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to both polyps and algae and between them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.42,0:07:37.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时也把荒凉的海洋变成了绚丽的花园\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they turn the barren seas into rich gardens.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.34,0:07:52.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,印度尼西亚的珊瑚礁之所以 容纳了如此多的海洋生物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Indonesian reefs contain such a variety of life
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.42,0:07:54.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它处在一个巨大的十字路口\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}because they lie at a giant crossroads.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.46,0:08:00.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是两个大洋的交汇处 印度洋和太平洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This is the meeting place for different seas the Indian Ocean and the Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.38,0:08:07.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这里,每样物种都要仔细观察\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here everything demands a closer look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.78,0:08:12.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这株海扇上,有2只"珊瑚虫"不像珊瑚虫\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}On the surface of this sea fan, there are two polyps that are not polyps.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.66,0:08:19.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,豆丁海马--全世界最小的海马,身长不到两公分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're pygmy sea horses, the world's smallest, less than two centimeters high.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.86,0:08:35.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这2只雄性豆丁海马正在为争夺领地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They are males, settling a territorial dispute,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:37.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相互撞头攻击\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}by head butting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.30,0:08:48.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,电光灯?\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An electric flash?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.94,0:08:52.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当然不是,这是火蛤蜊在表演\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}No, the display of a file clam.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.46,0:09:02.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蛤的肉质外壳的这种非常特别的规律性闪电\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Perhaps this extraordinary pulsation of the clam's fleshy mantle
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.50,0:09:05.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是在警告咬它的小鱼?\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is a warning to frighten away nibbling fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:07.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过真正原因无从知晓\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but no one really knows
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.42,0:09:26.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里也有蛇 许多的蛇\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And there are snakes here, too, lots of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.38,0:09:35.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是巨环海蛇\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are banded sea crates.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.86,0:09:40.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在陆地上产卵,在水里捕食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They lay their eggs on land but they hunt here in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.38,0:09:48.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们直接捕食鱼速度跟不上\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're too slow to catch fish in a straight chase
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.02,0:09:53.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此就在珊瑚礁的裂缝和暗处寻找猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so they seek prey that is hiding in the nooks and crannies of the coral.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.30,0:09:59.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的剧毒能立刻让受害者全身麻痹,动弹不得\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their bite is highly venomous and paralyzes their victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.26,0:10:09.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个珊瑚礁里,海蛇并不是单独行动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And on this reef the snakes do not hunt alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.46,0:10:20.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,许多的黄色绯鲵鲣和它的同伴们 也在寻找同样的猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Shoals of yellow goatfish and trivali are seeking similar prey
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.74,0:10:23.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们引起了海蛇的注意\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And they attract the snakes' attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:27.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们也加入进来,开始扫荡珊瑚礁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As one group of hunters searches the reef they're joined by the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.62,0:10:40.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,至少有30条海蛇加入到了这个队伍\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At least thirty snakes have now joined the caravan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.82,0:10:49.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大鱼将猎物吓到裂缝里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The big fish scare the prey into cracks
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.02,0:10:52.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里,海蛇就能抓住它们了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and there the snakes can catch them
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.62,0:10:58.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样从海蛇嘴里逃跑的猎物 也将直接送到这些大鱼嘴里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}And anything fleeing from the crates will swim straight into the mouths of the waiting trivali.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.22,0:11:01.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,猎物们没有地方可以躲藏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's nowhere to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.62,0:11:12.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有更多的海蛇加入进来一起扫荡珊瑚礁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As the raiders scour the reef, more and more snakes join the hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.58,0:11:37.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种鱼蛇之间的合作\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This cooperation between snakes and fish,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:45.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引人入胜.只是最近才被发现. 因为它发生在偏僻的印尼珊瑚礁\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}spectacular though it is, has only recently been observed, for it only happens on the most remote reefs in Indonesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.18,0:11:58.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许这种事情曾经发生在印尼的大多数珊瑚礁中.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Perhaps such hunting alliances were once a common sight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.78,0:12:04.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是到现在 只有不到6%的珊瑚礁还还保持着原始状态\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but today no more than six percent of Indonesia's reefs are in their pristine state.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.18,0:12:35.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在珊瑚礁上,是流砂的世界\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Beyond the coral stretches a world of shifting sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.26,0:12:40.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里无处可藏,要生存是很困难的事情\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Out there with nowhere to hide survival is not easy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.38,0:12:43.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以伪装变得至关重要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and camouflage can be crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.54,0:12:50.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这个家伙不动的话 你说不定会以为这是块贝壳或者石头.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}If this wasn't moving, you might think it was a shell or a rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.02,0:12:52.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,实际上,它是条章鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In fact it's an octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.10,0:12:59.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这条鲂鱼,它的巨大的胸鳍给它提供了很好的伪装\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A gurnard. It's huge pectoral fins disguise it's shape
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.82,0:13:03.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且它的胸鳍还可以在找寻食物的时候清理砂子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they can also help in clearing away sand when searching for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.70,0:13:11.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大颚鱼藏在地下.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The jawfish hides underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.78,0:13:21.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拟态章鱼用强有力的触手 摆出特别的姿势警告其他动物远离此地\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The wonderpus octopus on the other hand has such a powerful bite that it has a special warning display to tell others to keep out of it's way.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.34,0:13:37.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,植物设法到处生根\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Here and there, plants manage to take root
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.34,0:13:40.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们成了绿海龟的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they're cropped by green turtles.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.62,0:13:45.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海草是唯一在海里生长的有花植物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Seagrasses are the only flowering plants that have managed to grow in the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.58,0:13:55.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海草长出叶子状的带状物 以此延伸它们埋在沙子里的肉质根茎.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}although they put out a few ribbon like leaves they produce very extended networks of fleshy stems, risomes, that are buried in the sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.50,0:14:07.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种蓬勃的长势可以把海床覆盖在下面\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}At their lushest they can transform the sea bed into an underwater meadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.14,0:14:15.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,世界上最大的草海在澳大利亚西部的鲨鱼湾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The largest expanse grows in the shallow waters of Shark Bay, in Western Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.50,0:14:22.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这片广大的海洋牧场 面积可达1500平方英里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These vast aquatic grasslands stretch for fifteen hundred square miles
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.42,0:14:29.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,像陆地上的大草原一样 这里也养育了大量的食草动物--儒艮\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and, like terrestrial prairies, they support herds of grazers -- Dugongs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.42,0:14:46.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,儒艮是海洋里最大的食草动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Dugongs are the largest herbivores in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.94,0:14:49.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以长到3米长,半吨重\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They can be three meters long and weigh half a ton
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:56.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们除了海草什么都不吃 他们不停移动嘴唇,把海草的肉质根茎送到口中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they eat nothing but seagrass, mostly the fleshy risomes, which they excavate with their mobile lips.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.10,0:15:17.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这群儒艮可以在一天内吃掉足球场般大小的海草\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A herd can clear a patch of seagrass the size of a football pitch in a single day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.86,0:15:47.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,食物在热带海域的分布并不平均 所以要找到食物也不容易\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Food is not evenly distributed in the tropical shallow seas and it can take a lot of finding
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.54,0:15:54.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象宽吻海豚这种又好奇 又聪明伶俐又精神充沛的动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but bottlenose dolphins are inquisitive, energetic,1 and very intelligent
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.70,0:15:57.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发明了一种利用浅滩钓鱼的方法\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they have discovered a shoal of baitfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.42,0:16:09.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们一起赶着海浪,好让海浪把它们带到浅水域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Together, they ride a wave, using it to carry them into the shallows
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.34,0:16:13.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样,捕鱼就轻松多了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and there, it will be easier to make the catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.90,0:16:41.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在澳大利亚西部\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In Western Australia
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.74,0:16:45.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些海豚面临着一个巨大挑战\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}these dolphins have taken on an ever tougher challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.70,0:16:52.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鱼儿们太靠近沙滩,而那里的水才几厘米深\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The fish have taken refuge close to the beach where the water is only a few centimeters deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.90,0:17:01.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用有力的尾巴击晕猎物是海豚们常用的方法\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Tail slapping is a method dolphins often use to stun their prey
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.30,0:17:04.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过在这里好像没有什么用处\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it doesn't seem to work here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.58,0:17:19.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然已经很接近鱼儿了 急人的是还是差那么一点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The fish are tantalizingly close but they're still out of reach,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.78,0:17:22.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海豚于是开始用另一种技巧\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so the dolphins try another technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.46,0:17:31.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用他们有力的尾巴加速\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Vigorously pumping their tails, they work up some speed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.18,0:17:34.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如同水上飞机般\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and then, they hydroplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.74,0:18:06.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种速度让它们穿越最浅的水域, 来到了鱼儿那里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Their momentum carries them right through the shallowest waters, and onto the fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.02,0:18:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在它们有搁浅的危险\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Now they're in real danger of being stranded
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.90,0:18:24.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但幸运来自勇气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but fortune favors the brave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.90,0:18:35.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,年轻的海豚在远处观看\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Younger dolphins lie alongside, watching
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.02,0:18:41.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不远处有8只海豚在展示这种高超的技术\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but so far only eight individuals here have mastered this daring technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.78,0:19:38.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虽然多数热带海洋生物 聚集在珊瑚礁或者海洋牧场里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Although most life in tropical waters is concentrated around the coral reefs and the seagrass meadows,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.30,0:19:40.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过还有些例外引人入胜.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}there are some spectacular exceptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.50,0:19:49.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,巴林的戈壁沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The desert of Bahrain seems a very unlikely place
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.58,0:19:54.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看上去不象是能有大量海鸟筑巢的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to find a crowded bustling colony of seabirds
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.62,0:20:00.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可每年大约有10万只黑喉鸬鹚在这里繁殖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But every year, a hundred thousand socotra cormorants gather here to breed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.34,0:20:09.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里相当酷热\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's swelteringly hot
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.94,0:20:14.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黑喉鸬鹚只好加速呼吸避免中暑\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and only vigorous panting can prevent the birds from fatal overheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.70,0:20:19.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看上去这里不是抚育后代的好地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}This hardly seems a good place to rear young
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.10,0:20:24.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过至少没有陆基的捕食者\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but at least, there are no land based predators here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.06,0:20:28.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麻烦的唯一来源可能就是邻居了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The only source of trouble is likely to be the neighbors
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.70,0:20:33.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以每一个鸟窝都筑在邻居啄不到的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}so each nest is built just beyond pecking reach
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.26,0:20:49.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,食物从哪里来呢?\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But what about food?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.42,0:20:54.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个荒凉沙漠远离温暖的浅海\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There's only bare sand and the warm shallow sea beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.94,0:21:00.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而且看上去也不能提供给鸬鹚足够的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Neither seem likely to produce enough nourishment to support bird life on this scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.58,0:21:07.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,答案是刮起的大风\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The answer is blowing in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.22,0:21:16.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夏马风卷起沙尘 吹向波斯湾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sand whipped up by Shamals offshore winds blows into the seas of the Arabian Gulf.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.22,0:21:25.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,风把带着养分的沙尘,像肥料一样撒进大海, 把这片浅海变成了富饶的渔场.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With the grains come nutrients, which act as fertilizer and they transform the shallow sea into a rich fishing ground
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.86,0:21:35.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,矛盾的是 热浪朝天的的阿拉伯半岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}So, paradoxically, it's the roasted sands of Arabia that prevent the gulf
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.30,0:21:39.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阻止海湾变成另一个海中沙漠\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}from being another desert in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.34,0:21:55.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小座头鲸现在有五个月大了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The whale calf is now five months old.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.62,0:22:02.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的身材也大了一倍 在热带托儿所的日子也到头了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}He's almost doubled in size and his days in his tropical nursery are coming to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.06,0:22:06.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这个地方长大温暖而安全\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It has been a warm and safe place in which to grow up
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.50,0:22:09.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在这里他的母亲无法吃到任何东西\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but there's nothing to eat here for his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.58,0:22:15.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她在过去的八个月里一直靠储存的脂肪存活\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She has been living off her fat reserves for the last eight months
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.18,0:22:18.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在她临近饿死的边缘\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and she's close to starving.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.30,0:22:24.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,她现在必须离开 趁她还有足够的能量 在漫漫征途之中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}She must leave now, while she still has enough energy to guide and protect her calf,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.00,0:22:26.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来指导和保护她的幼子\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}on the long voyage ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.58,0:22:47.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,横越热带 座头鲸调头离开赤道\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}All across the tropics, humpbacks are heading away
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.00,0:22:54.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,走向富饶而气候温和的南半球和北半球海域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}from the Equator towards the rich temperate seas of both the southern and the northern hemispheres.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.42,0:23:01.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些是更冷、更狂暴、更多危险的水域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are colder, rougher, and more dangerous waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.14,0:23:16.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,母鲸和小鲸鱼必须靠得很近\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Mother and calf must stay close.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.42,0:23:39.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们可以通过拍打海面 制造超越海洋轰鸣的的声音\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They can send sound signals to one another, above the roar of the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.54,0:23:41.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以此相互传送声音信号\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}by slapping fins on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.38,0:24:07.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在冬季 气候温和的海域被风暴肆虐着\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In winter, the temperate seas are lashed by violent storms.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.78,0:24:31.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,湍流激起海水 将深处的养分搅上来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The turbulence stirs the water, and draws nutrients up from the depths
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.06,0:24:43.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但只有养分并不能维持生命\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but nutrients alone can not support life.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.50,0:24:46.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还必须有阳光\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}There must also be sunlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.02,0:24:53.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,春天 太阳高悬空中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the spring, as the sun daily climbs higher in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.94,0:24:55.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,藻类开始生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the algae start to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.34,0:25:02.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,旺盛的藻类占据着亚马逊雨林般大小的面积 它们将大海染绿\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Blooms the size of the Amazon Rainforest turn the seas green.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.54,0:25:13.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,单体藻类虽然很细小 但它们共同产生了我们大气中四分之三的氧气\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Individually the algae are tiny but together, they produce three quarters of all the oxygen in our atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.06,0:25:21.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,藻类被一群让人困惑的生物吃掉\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're eaten by an array of bewildering creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.10,0:25:27.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,樽海鞘出现在浮游生物汤中\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Salps appear in the plankton soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.62,0:25:36.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些一个个单体组成的链条可长达15米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Individuals link together to form chains which can stretch for fifteen meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.98,0:25:52.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们用汲取海水,在身体里过滤 分离出藻类及其他可食用微粒\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Pumping water through their bodies they strain out algae and other edible particles.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.34,0:26:05.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,栉水母在水中游弋,\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Comb jellies cruise through the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.50,0:26:09.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们也在这个季节性美汤里蓬勃生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They too flourish in this seasonal soup
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.30,0:26:13.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在很短的时间内,它们就能达到惊人的数量.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and for short periods, they appear in astounding numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.46,0:26:20.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磷虾,一种小型虾类,如果按重量计算\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Krill, shrimp like creatures. By weight they're the most
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.00,0:26:24.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们是地球上最多量的动物,一群就可达200万吨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}abundant animals on the planet. A single swarm can contain two million tons of them
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.82,0:26:36.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,磷虾也为鱼提供了大量的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that is a lot of fish food.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.42,0:26:50.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这片温和的浅海是地球上鱼类最密集的地区\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The shallow temperate seas support the greatest concentrations of fish on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.02,0:26:55.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大量鱼群从海洋深处的冬歇地赶来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Huge shoals migrate from their overwintering grounds in the depths
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.86,0:26:58.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这片富饶海域进食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to feed in these rich waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.42,0:27:12.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鱼群也养育了世界上大多数海洋哺乳动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It's these shoals that support most of the world's sea mammals.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.10,0:27:18.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海狮拥有捕鱼所需的敏捷和速度\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sea lions have all the agility and speed needed to collect what they want
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.50,0:27:21.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看起来他们也喜欢这样做\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and seemingly delight in doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.26,0:28:02.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,200条暗色斑纹海豚聚集在一起 紧密合作,尽情收获\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Dusky dolphin, often in pods two hundred strong work together to reap the harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.66,0:28:11.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们将鱼群分成许多小群, 让猎人们更加易于处理.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They break up the shoals into smaller, more manageable balls, and all the hunters benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.70,0:28:42.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直到夏至 海洋表面的养分全部被摄取\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}By midsummer, the surface nutrients have all been absorbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.82,0:28:46.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,藻类死亡 食物链因此崩溃\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The algae die and the food chain collapses.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.82,0:28:53.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而在少数特别的地方\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In a few special places, however
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.34,0:28:58.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,气候温和的海域维持这个生命水平贯穿整个夏季\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the temperate seas sustain these levels of life throughout the summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.46,0:29:04.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在加利福尼亚沿海 洋流持续不断的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Along the coast of California, ocean currents carry a constant
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.00,0:29:06.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把养分从海底 带到海平面上来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}supply of nutrients up from the depths to the surface layers.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.54,0:29:15.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这种上升洋流给巨藻带来了大量养分 在夏日阳光照射下它们飞速生长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These upwellings fertilize forests of giant kelp, that thrive in the summer sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.82,0:29:25.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这片巨藻林有足有三层楼那么高\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The algal towers are as high as a three story house
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.82,0:29:28.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们每天还能长半米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they can grow by half a meter a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.22,0:29:47.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海藻中的生命充满戏剧性 跟其他森林一样\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Life in the kelp is as full of drama, as in any other forest
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.46,0:29:51.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但演员们仍不太为人知.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but the cast is less familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.86,0:29:55.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一大群紫海胆正在发动进攻\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}An army of sea urchins is mounting an attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.30,0:30:04.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海胆们正在吃巨藻的固着器 把巨藻固定在石头上的重要装置\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The urchin plague strikes at the kelp's holdfasts their crucial attachments to the rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.46,0:30:21.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,固着器非常坚硬\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Holdfasts are extremely tough,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.06,0:30:27.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是每只海胆有5个锋利的牙齿 而且每隔几个月就换牙\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but each urchin has five teeth, which are self sharpening and are replaced every few months.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.30,0:30:43.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海胆吃掉了大片的海藻森林 把它们变成了不毛之地.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Urchins fell vast areas of kelp forest creating clearings know as urchin barrens
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.14,0:30:50.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无法形容的荒凉.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}yet barrens is a poor description.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.58,0:30:58.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,百万只无脊椎动物侵袭了海床\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Millions of invertebrates invade the seabed.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.18,0:31:15.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里有可怕的大型掠食动物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The most fearsome predator here is a giant.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.58,0:31:23.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向日葵海星长达1米 它喜欢吃蛇尾海星\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The sunflower starfish is a meter across, with an appetite for brittle stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.18,0:31:44.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向日葵海星用触角来试探猎物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}It uses it's feet to taste for prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.70,0:31:51.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在快速镜头下\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}When it's actions are speeded up,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.42,0:31:55.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以清楚看到向日葵海星喜欢吃蛇尾海星\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}it becomes clear that the predator's fondness for the brittle stars
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.50,0:31:59.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这与蛇尾海星快速逃离现场也是相吻合的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}is almost matched by the brittle stars ability to get out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.90,0:32:17.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成群的饼海胆叠加起来组成防御阵线\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Sand dollars flat sea urchins cluster together as a defense
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.66,0:32:27.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过好像在向日葵海星面前没有作用\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But it doesn't seem to work against the sunflower starfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.38,0:32:34.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向日葵海星挤出它的胃 包住饼海胆直接消化其软组织\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The predator extrudes it's stomach, and wraps it around it's victims liquefying their soft parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.02,0:32:38.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最后只剩下饼海胆的白色骨架.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Nothing is left of them, except their white skeletons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.30,0:32:50.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加利福尼亚寒流是季节性洋流,相对较小.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Californian upwellings are seasonal and relatively small
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.66,0:32:59.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过在南部非洲的大洋流带来的 充足食物能满足百万只海豹的需要\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but in Southern Africa they're so big they create seas rich enough to support colonies of over a million seals.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.78,0:33:10.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,本格拉寒流--沿南部非洲西岸流动\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Benguela Current sweeps along the western coastline of Southern Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.00,0:33:13.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,给海洋表面带来充足养分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}driving nutrient rich waters up to the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.02,0:33:21.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后,在非洲南端(好望角)与 沿非洲大陆以南海域流动的厄加勒斯暖流汇合\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and then, at the southern tip of Africa it meets the Agulhas Current, arriving from the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.26,0:33:24.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,结果是,海洋养分更加丰富.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The result: even richer waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.94,0:33:41.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海豹在吃这里大量的鱼和枪乌贼(即鱿鱼)\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The seals here thrive on a diet of fish and squid.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.90,0:33:48.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这块海洋里,鱿鱼实际上要比鱼类多.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In temperate seas there may actually be more squid than fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.06,0:33:57.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是宽褶鱿鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}These are choker squid,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.14,0:34:04.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们在厄加勒斯暖流经过的砂质浅海处产卵\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and they lay their egg capsules in sandy shallows bathed by the warmer Agulhas Current.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.46,0:34:17.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每个卵囊都有100多条小鱿鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each capsule contains a hundred tiny squid.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.94,0:34:27.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几天后它们长出一些色斑 等到成熟后\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Within a few days they develop spots of pigment which, when they're adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.00,0:34:30.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就可以用这些色斑来互相联系\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they will use to communicate with one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.22,0:34:44.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雌鱿鱼继续产卵\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With females continuing to lay eggs
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.22,0:34:51.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,雄鱿鱼则忙于击退竞争对手而放松了警惕\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and males still preoccupied with repelling rivals, the squid drop their guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.34,0:34:56.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黄貂鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Stingray.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.46,0:35:07.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,短尾黄貂鱼身长可达2米\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Short tailed stingray can be up to two meters across.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.46,0:35:19.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是世界上最大的一种? 与之相称的还有它的胃口\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They're the largest of all the stingrays, and they have appetites to match.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.74,0:35:50.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还有掠食者在游弋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Another predator is on the prowl.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.66,0:35:55.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,南非虎头鲨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The aptly named ragged tooth shark.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.38,0:36:02.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,虎头鲨可以长到3米长\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Raggies grow to three meters long,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.46,0:36:06.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过还有2倍于它的鲨鱼 在和它们一起分享这片水域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they share these waters with a shark twice their size.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.38,0:36:25.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大白鲨\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The great white.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.30,0:36:30.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上最大的掠食性鱼类\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The largest predatory fish on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.34,0:36:41.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,黎明时分,南非海狗离开聚居地去捕鱼\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each dawn cape fur seals leave their colony to go fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.50,0:36:44.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要到达远海\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}To reach the open sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.10,0:36:47.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们必须穿越一片狭窄的水域\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}they must cross a narrow strip of water
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.50,0:36:51.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大白鲨就在那里逡巡\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and that is patrolled by great whites.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.26,0:37:04.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每只海豹必须拼命游泳\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Each seal is indeed swimming for it's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.66,0:37:29.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可大白鲨让人惊奇\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The shark relies on surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.26,0:38:33.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大白鲨的速度和力量来自体内高速的新陈代谢\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The great white's turn of speed is powered by a high metabolism.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.30,0:38:41.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们只呆在冰冷的海里 也只有大海才有充足的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}They only thrive in cold temperate seas for only these waters contain sufficient food necessary
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.00,0:38:43.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,供这种贪婪的掠食者享用\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}to fuel such a ravenous predator.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.18,0:39:22.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当你朝南北两极旅行 更冷,更多风暴的海域才是更加富饶的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}As you travel towards the poles north or south the colder, stormier seas can become even richer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.46,0:39:28.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在南非和南极之间\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Midway between South Africa and the South Pole
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.22,0:39:32.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有一个与世隔绝的岛屿--马里恩岛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}lies the isolated island of Marion.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.34,0:39:41.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,岛屿位于气候恶劣的"咆哮西风带"\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The island sits in the infamous "roaring forties"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.30,0:39:50.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不间断的大风把海底的养分送上来 从而给帝企鹅提供了丰富的食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}where incessant gale force winds draw nutrients up from the depths ensuring plenty of food for king penguins.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.50,0:39:56.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,帝企鹅刚刚完成了3天的捕捞航行\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The kings are returning from a three day fishing trip,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.66,0:39:58.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并给孩子们带来了食物\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}with food for their chicks
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.06,0:40:02.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过首先它们要通过拥挤的海滩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}But first they must cross a crowded beach,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.22,0:40:07.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从巨大的,暴躁的海象间开出一条路来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}threading their way between gigantic and bad tempered elephant seals.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.34,0:40:24.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在这块富饶的捕鱼圣地上 大约有20万只企鹅在这里繁殖\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The two hundred thousand penguins breeding here are testament to the richness of the fishing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.74,0:40:36.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小帝企鹅必须依靠它们的母亲至少一年 这给它们父母带来巨大的压力\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}King chicks are dependent on their mothers for over a year and this puts a great deal of pressure on the parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.26,0:40:55.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于不能飞 企鹅必须步行穿越空旷的海滩\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Being flightless, the returning penguins must cross the open beach on foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.90,0:41:31.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海狗,来到海滩繁殖并等待企鹅的到来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Fur seals, that have come to the beach to breed, are waiting for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.50,0:41:42.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通常海狗以磷虾为生\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Fur seals normally live on krill
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.26,0:41:48.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过现在.它们可以从富含鲸脂的企鹅身上 获得意想不到的美味\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but these have now acquired an unexpected taste for blubber rich penguins.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.42,0:42:42.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,企鹅在海狗面前可能是轻量级选手\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Penguins may be featherweights by comparison
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.38,0:42:45.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是企鹅有尖利的喙和易怒的性格\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but they have razor sharp bills and a feisty character.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.54,0:42:51.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,海狗可能会被啄瞎眼睛\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The seal could easily lose an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.98,0:42:57.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,唯一的方法就是从背后抓住企鹅 不过企鹅也很清楚这一点.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The only safe way to grab a penguin is from behind, and the birds are well aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.54,0:43:24.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,两种动物在这地形下都显得笨拙 不过企鹅更容易失败\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Both animals are clumsy on this terrain but the penguin has the more to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.82,0:43:37.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成功了!\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.10,0:43:45.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有三分之二的企鹅能在海狗的攻击下逃生 顺利到达永远吃不饱的小企鹅身边\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Two out of three penguins survive the seal attacks and succeed in reaching their ever hungry chicks.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.42,0:44:19.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,座头鲸接近它们史诗般旅程的终点\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The humpbacks are nearing the end of their epic journeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.78,0:44:32.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,历时2个月,数千英里的跋涉 它们进入了两极的极地海洋\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}After two months and thousands of miles, they're entering the polar seas both in the north and the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.78,0:44:47.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在遥远的北方 寒冬终于过去\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In the far north, winter is over at last
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.82,0:44:49.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,冰雪开始消融\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the ice is starting to melt.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.14,0:45:00.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿拉斯加(美国)西部的 阿留申群岛是通向白令海的大门\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The Aleutian Island chain running west from Alaska is the gateway to the Bearing Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.54,0:45:06.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着冰雪的消退,暴烈的天气 和汹涌的洋流把这片浅海搅得天翻地覆\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With the retreating ice, rough weather and ferocious currents stir up these shallow seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.34,0:45:11.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,再加上阳光,这种组合的产生了大量的养分\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Add sunshine and the mix is spectacularly productive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.82,0:45:27.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,500万只水雉鸟 从澳大利亚飞行了近万英里来到这里\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Five million shearwaters have flown almost ten thousand miles from Australia to get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.22,0:45:32.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,总计约有8000万只海鸟到这里度夏\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}In all eighty million seabirds come here for the summer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.34,0:45:36.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到处都是世界上最伟大的聚集\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}the greatest concentration to be found anywhere on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.30,0:45:52.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,座头鲸终于抵达\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The humpbacks have finally arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.34,0:46:15.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,庞大的水雉鸟群大量捕食磷虾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The giant shearwater flocks hunt the krill swarms
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.38,0:46:19.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有时它们潜到40米深\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}sometimes diving to depths of forty meters to reach them.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.58,0:46:46.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一头成年座头鲸每天能吃掉3吨磷虾\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}A large humpback eats three tons of krill a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.50,0:47:03.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,夏季的极地海域是地球上最多产的\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The polar seas in summer are the most productive on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.78,0:47:06.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鲸鱼昼夜不停地在此进食\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}and the whales gorge themselves round the clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.30,0:47:16.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们现在积累的脂肪\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}The fat reserves they lay down now
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.86,0:47:18.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可以支持到明年再来\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}will keep them alive during the year to come
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.82,0:47:22.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过也可能不会再来了\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}but it may not always be this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.42,0:47:31.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,鱼和磷虾的产量正在迅速减少 象这样的景象可能很快将成为历史\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Fish and krill stocks are declining so rapidly that spectacles like this may soon be part of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.46,0:47:46.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦母鲸和小鲸到达他们的给养地 它们就要分开\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}Once the mother and calf have reached their feeding grounds, they will separate.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.10,0:47:55.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果幸运的话 小座头鲸还要把从赤道到极地的史诗般旅程\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}With luck, the calf will make the epic journey across the oceans from equator to pole
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.42,0:47:57.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,重复70次\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}another seventy times
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.10,0:48:05.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让我们在浅海之间来回巡游 赞叹于地球生命的丰富多彩.\N{\fs54\1c&HFFFF00&\b0}cruising back and forth between the shallow seas where life proliferates so abundantly on our planet.

